<subSubSection pageNumber="873" type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="873">
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="873">Note:</emphasis>
Erben (in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="873">
Mitt. Bot. Staatssamml. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="München">Muenchen</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
14: 447. 1978; 27: 396. 1988) treated 395.16 (LINN) as the type. However, there seems little to link this Scopoli collection, received by Linnaeus around 1762-63, with the protologue apart from Linnaeus 
<normalizedToken originalValue="filius’">filius'</normalizedToken>
determination. Erben (1988) excluded 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Linnaeus’">Linnaeus'</normalizedToken>
cited synonyms and evidently uses the name in a sense entirely different from that employed by Pignatti (in Tutin &amp; al., 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="873">Fl. Europaea 3</emphasis>
: 43. 1972), and previously (1978) by Erben himself. In 1988, he described 
<emphasis italics="true" pageNumber="873">L. pseudominutum</emphasis>
Erben for that taxon.
</paragraph>
